# skill: qa-report
# purpose: Generate quality report (QA Persona - Phase 4)
# triggers: Validation complete

## Invocation
```
qa-report <task-id> [--validation <validation-file>] [--format <md|json>]
```

## Output
Creates: `memory/tasks/<task-id>/quality-report.md` or JSON

## Implementation Flow

### 1. Load Context
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# qa-report.skill implementation

TASK_ID="$1"
VALIDATION_FILE="${2:-memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/validation-report.md}"

if [ ! -f "$VALIDATION_FILE" ]; then
    echo "Error: Validation report not found"
    exit 1
fi

VALIDATION=$(cat "$VALIDATION_FILE")
```

### 2. Generate Quality Report
```markdown
# Quality Report: <task-id>

## Executive Summary
| Metric | Status |
|--------|--------|
| Overall Quality | ✓ PASS | ⚠ WARN | ✗ FAIL |
| Test Pass Rate | <rate>% |
| Code Coverage | <coverage>% |
| Critical Issues | <count> |

## Detailed Results

### Test Coverage
$(grep -A 20 "## Failed Tests" "$VALIDATION_FILE" | head -25)

### Code Quality Metrics
| Metric | Value | Threshold | Status |
|--------|-------|---|---|
| Test Coverage | <coverage>% | 80% | ✓/✗ |
| Test Pass Rate | <rate>% | 100% | ✓/✗ |
| Code Smells | <count> | 0 | ✓/✗ |
| Security Issues | <count> | 0 | ✓/✗ |

### Risk Assessment
| Risk | Level | Mitigated |
|------|-------|---|
| <risk> | <H/M/L> | ✓/✗ |

### Acceptance Criteria Status
| AC | Status | Evidence |
|----|---|---|
| AC1 | ✓ PASS | [Test results](#) |
| AC2 | ✓ PASS | [Test results](#) |

### Defects Found
| ID | Severity | Description | Status |
|----|---|---|---|
| DEF-1 | <H/M/L> | <description> | Fixed/Open |

## Recommendations
### Must Fix (Blocking)
- [ ] <blocking item 1>
- [ ] <blocking item 2>

### Should Fix (Recommended)
- [ ] <item 1>
- [ ] <item 2>

### Could Fix (Nice to Have)
- [ ] <item 1>
- [ ] <item 2>

## Approval
**QA Sign-off:** ✓ APPROVED | ⚠ APPROVED WITH NOTES | ✗ REJECTED

**Notes:**
<any additional notes for stakeholders>

**Generated:** $(date +%Y-%m-%d)
**QA Engineer:** <agent-name>
```

### 3. Output
```bash
FORMAT="${2:-md}"

if [ "$FORMAT" = "json" ]; then
    # Output JSON format
    jq -n \
        --arg task_id "$TASK_ID" \
        --arg pass_rate "$PASSED_RATE" \
        --arg coverage "$COVERAGE" \
        --arg status "$STATUS" \
        '{
            task_id: $task_id,
            quality_status: $status,
            test_pass_rate: $pass_rate,
            code_coverage: $coverage
        }'
else
    cat "memory/tasks/$TASK_ID/quality-report.md"
fi
```
